cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is about visual object tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper proposes a novel network architecture that utilizes gradient information for template update, which involves machine learning techniques. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. The paper also evaluates its method on several benchmark datasets, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.RO (Robotics).
